{"slug":"sirkuler-25-0712eng","reference":"Sirkuler_25_0712ENG","gazette":"White House","title":"President Donald J. Trump signed an Executive Order modifying the scope of the reciprocal tariffs","date":"06 Eylül 2025","bodyHtml":"<p class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\">President Donald J. Trump has signed&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.whitehouse.gov/presidential-actions/2025/09/modifying-the-scope-of-reciprocal-tariffs-and-establishing-procedures-for-implementing-trade-and-security-agreements/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"custom-cursor-on-hover\" style=\"text-decoration-line: underline; font-weight: bold;\">a new Executive Order&nbsp;</a>modifying the scope of the reciprocal tariffs first announced on April 2, 2025, and establishing a framework for implementing trade agreements with U.S. partners.</p><p class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\">Scope of reciprocal tariffs updated.</p><p class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\">On April 2, historic global reciprocal tariffs were imposed to address the national emergency posed by America’s large and persistent trade deficit.</p><p class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\"><span class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\" style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration-line: underline;\">Today’s Order revises Annex II:</span></p><ul class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\"><li class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\">Added to Annex II (tariff exemptions): bullion-related articles, certain critical minerals, and pharmaceutical products subject to ongoing Section 232 investigations.</li><li class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\">Removed from Annex II (newly tariffed): certain aluminum hydroxide, resin, and silicone products.</li></ul><p class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\">These changes will take effect&nbsp;<span class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\" style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration-line: underline;\">on September 8, 2025</span>.</p><p class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\"><span class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\" style=\"text-decoration-line: underline; font-weight: bold;\">Creation of the “Potential Tariff Adjustments for Aligned Partners” (PTAAP) list.</span></p><p class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\">This list identifies products that may be reduced to the Most-Favored-Nation (MFN) tariff rate once a reciprocal trade and security deal is concluded:</p><ul class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\"><li class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\">Certain aircraft and aircraft parts</li><li class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\">Certain generic pharmaceuticals and their ingredients</li><li class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\">Unavailable natural resources and derivative products</li><li class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\">Agricultural products not sufficiently produced in the U.S.</li></ul><p class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\">Tariff reductions tied to commitments. A trading partner must conclude a deal with the U.S. that helps mitigate the trade deficit emergency.</p><p class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\"><span class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\" style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration-line: underline;\">Previous Tariff Actions</span></p><ul class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\"><li class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\">20% tariff on China – synthetic opioid supply chain.</li><li class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\">25% tariff on Mexico and 35% tariff on Canada – illicit drug flows across borders.</li><li class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\">40% tariff on Brazil – recent actions threatening U.S. security and economy.</li><li class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\">25% tariff on India – continued purchase of Russian oil.</li><li class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\">Section 232 tariffs on automobiles, auto parts, copper, steel, and aluminum – protecting strategic industries.</li></ul><p class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\"><a href=\"https://www.whitehouse.gov/fact-sheets/2025/09/fact-sheet-president-donald-j-trump-modifies-the-scope-of-reciprocal-tariffs-and-establishes-procedures-for-implementing-trade-deals/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"custom-cursor-on-hover\" style=\"text-decoration-line: underline; font-weight: bold;\">Click for the factsheet published by White House.</a></p><p class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\" style=\"text-wrap: pretty; margin-block: 30.9744px 0px; max-width: 808.024px; color: rgb(41, 51, 64); font-family: &quot;Instrument Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 18.6768px; letter-spacing: 0.2px; margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><span class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\" style=\"text-decoration-line: underline; font-weight: bold;\">HTSUS newly added to the exemption list ANNEX II&nbsp;</span></p><figure class=\"wp-block-table\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-x: auto; --wh--block--table--padding: 12px; margin-block: 30.9744px 0px; max-width: 808.024px; color: rgb(41, 51, 64); font-family: &quot;Instrument Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 18.6768px; letter-spacing: 0.2px; margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout custom-cursor-default-hover\" style=\"width: 808.013px; table-layout: fixed; border-color: rgb(41, 51, 64) !important;\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\" style=\"padding: 0.5em; border: 1px solid; padding-block: 12px; padding-inline: 12px; word-break: break-word;\">2504.10.10</td></tr><tr><td class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\" style=\"padding: 0.5em; border: 1px solid; padding-block: 12px; padding-inline: 12px; word-break: break-word;\">2604.00.00</td></tr><tr><td class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\" style=\"padding: 0.5em; border: 1px solid; padding-block: 12px; padding-inline: 12px; word-break: break-word;\">2609.00.00</td></tr><tr><td class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\" style=\"padding: 0.5em; border: 1px solid; padding-block: 12px; padding-inline: 12px; word-break: break-word;\">2612.20.00</td></tr><tr><td class=\"custom-cursor-default-hover\" style=\"padding: 0.5em; border: 1px solid; padding-block: 12px; pa